subSubSection.paragraph:
Sternohyoideus posterior tip 11.8%, sternohyoideus-heart gap 0.26, heart 3.9% (MP = 17.8%), snout-heart interval 19.8%, heart-liver gap 11.1%, liver lobes multipartite, right liver 39.6% (MP = 50.5%) with 45.5 (41– 50) segments, left liver 36.8% (MP = 50.9%) with 43.3 (41–45) segments, vena cava straight anteriorly and posteriorly but wavy along mid-third of liver, anterior liver extension 0.04, posterior liver tail 0.03, left liver = 0.94 right liver, liver-gall bladder gap 0.6, gall bladder 1.0% (MP = 71.4%
)
adjacent to pancreas (1.2%) and caudad of juxtasplenic body (1.3%) and spleen (1.3%), testes compact but multipartite, right testis 4.5% (MP = 79.3%) with 12.0 segments (11–13), left testis 4.0% (MP = 82.5%) with 11.7 segments (9–14), right ovary 4.8% (MP = 77.8%) with 1.5 (1–2) vitellogenic ova and 7.0 (3–12) follicles, right ovary 4.4% (MP = 82.1%) with 7 ova and one follicle, left ovary 4.0% (MP = 84.9%) with 4 ova, right adrenal MP = 82.7%, left adrenal MP = 84.6%, kidneys smooth but creased with one renal artery, right kidney 3.2% (MP = 85.6%), left kidney 3.0% (MP = 87.7%), kidney overlap 0.18, kidney-vent interval 16.0%, kidney-vent gap 10.8%, rectal caecum 1.0%, 2–5 times the diameter of adjacent small intestine, caecum-vent interval 10.2%.
